A man is in a critical condition following an apparent hijacking outside his residence on Sanders Street in New Germany, KwaZulu-Natal.On arrival to the scene, paramedics found the man in the garden of his property. It was found that he had sustained two gunshot wounds to his neck and face.It was found that he had sustained two gunshot wounds to his neck and face.The man was provided with advanced life support interventions.Once he was treated, he was then transported to Hillcrest Private Hospital for further treatment. Local authorities were on the scene to conduct an investigation into the cause of this incident.Local authorities were on the scene to conduct an investigation into the cause of the incident.-TNA Reporter 